<h3 id="coping-saw">Coping saw</h3>

<p>A faster way to removing the waste is by using a coping saw. You can use a thin blade to fit into the kerf (slit from the previous cuts) but I prefer using a thicker saw, which makes wider turns but cut faster. In this way the bulk of the waste material before the chiseling stage.</p>

